  displayName: Bakunawa
  description: Bakunawa is a colossal serpent-like being in Visayan mythology, most
    widely remembered for devouring moons and causing eclipses. Its imagery connects
    oceanic depth, celestial disruption, and cosmic imbalance in a single mythic
    form. Beyond creature lore, Bakunawa occupies an explanatory role in traditional
    storytelling, linking astronomical events to spiritual and moral order.
